From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Doe <john.doe@somewhere.on.planet>
Date: Fri, 28 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: clk: rockchip: rk3588: allow DCLK_VOP3 to retune parent PLL

DCLK_VOP3 is defined with flags=0, which means clk_set_rate() cannot
propagate to the parent PLL. The vendor kernel works around this with
a custom clock management layer that explicitly reparents dclk_vop3 to
v0pll and retunes v0pll directly (commit 842ad2732d2a). Mainline has
no such custom layer.

Add CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT | CLK_SET_RATE_NO_REPARENT to match DCLK_VOP2,
so the clock framework can propagate rate requests to the parent PLL.
Board DTS must use assigned-clock-parents to set v0pll as the parent,
since CLK_SET_RATE_NO_REPARENT prevents automatic reparenting.

Also add a PLL rate table entry for 268555184 Hz (fractional mode:
p=1, m=179, s=4, k=2411) so v0pll can produce exact MIPI DSI pixel
clocks. Without this entry, the PLL can only be set to the pre-defined
rates in the table, and the closest match produces ~134.1 MHz instead
of the required ~134.3 MHz for 59.94 Hz refresh.

Signed-off-by: John Doe <john.doe@somewhere.on.planet>
---
 drivers/clk/rockchip/clk-rk3588.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk-rk3588.c b/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk-rk3588.c
index 4bfc7d33e788..9a12ba06a8b1 100644
--- a/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk-rk3588.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk-rk3588.c
@@ -92,5 +92,6 @@ static struct rockchip_pll_rate_table rk3588_pll_rates[] = {
 	RK3588_PLL_RATE(312000000, 2, 208, 3, 0),
+	RK3588_PLL_RATE(268555184, 1, 179, 4, 2411),
 	RK3588_PLL_RATE(216000000, 2, 288, 4, 0),
 	RK3588_PLL_RATE(100000000, 3, 400, 5, 0),
 	RK3588_PLL_RATE(96000000, 2, 256, 5, 0),
 	{ /* sentinel */ },
@@ -2112,7 +2113,7 @@ static struct rockchip_clk_branch rk3588_clk_branches[] __initdata = {
 			CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT | CLK_SET_RATE_NO_REPARENT,
 			RK3588_CLKSEL_CON(112), 11, 2, MFLAGS,
 			RK3588_CLKGATE_CON(53), 1, GFLAGS),
-	COMPOSITE(DCLK_VOP3, "dclk_vop3", gpll_cpll_v0pll_aupll_p, 0,
+	COMPOSITE(DCLK_VOP3, "dclk_vop3", gpll_cpll_v0pll_aupll_p, CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT | CLK_SET_RATE_NO_REPARENT,
 			RK3588_CLKSEL_CON(113), 7, 2, MFLAGS, 0, 7, DFLAGS,
 			RK3588_CLKGATE_CON(53), 2, GFLAGS),
 	GATE(PCLK_DSIHOST0, "pclk_dsihost0", "pclk_vop_root", 0,
